wp-updater-xfce
Wallpaper Auto Updater by Aaron Blakely <aaron@ephasic.org>

This script will auto update your XFCE backdrop with a random image
from a defined directory at a defined interval.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This code is public domain.  You are free to modify or do whatever
you want wit it.

-------------------------------------------------------------------

Installing:
	1) Edit the configuration vars in the top of wp-update.sh
	2) Put the script in what you defined as RUNDIR
	3) chmod +x it
	4) Run it!

Optional:
	Add . ~/.wp-updater/auto-runner.sh to the end of your
	~/.bashrc to start this script on login.

	This is assuming you put the scripts into ~/.wp-updater
